cs.IR, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.CL 

The paper is about video recommendation, which is a subfield of information retrieval (IR) and multimedia (MM). The proposed model involves incorporating user-video interactions and various rich contents (e.g., text, audio, motion) to make recommendations, which requires techniques from machine learning (LG) and computer vision (CV) as well as natural language processing (CL) for processing text. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IR, followed by cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.CV, and cs.CL.
